@robpike, opinions on this?

I just got a CL to "fix" my formats from %p to %T to workaround this, but I had %p intentionally so I could line up interface values in my logs with leaked goroutine stack traces.

But I realize https://golang.org/pkg/fmt/ doesn't really define what %p means for an interface. Is it the second word of the interface value, assuming there's a pointer in there?
